<HEADLINE>
<P>
ON THE COVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Generations," a new daytime soap, joins the NBC lineup Monday at 11:30 a.m. on 
Channels 4, 36 and 39. 
</P>
<P>
It's the story of a white family, the Whitmores, and a black family, the 
Marshalls, whose lives have been linked for several generations in Chicago. 
</P>
<P>
The serial was created by Sally Sussman, a former writer for "The Young and the 
Restless." 
</P>
</TEXT>
