<P>
CONTINENTAL DIVIDED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kathie Jenkins 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Radicchio and quiche may come and go but Continental is here to stay. 
</P>
<P>
Cyril's of Los Angeles, 740 S. La Brea, Los Angeles. (213) 552-9745. Style: 
Enormous feasting of Continental Southern. Setting: Liberace visits the Cotton 
Club. Recommended dishes: Meat loaf, pan-fried catfish. Cost per person: 
$15-$25. 
</P>
<P>
Europa, 14929 Magnolia, Sherman Oaks. (818) 501-9175. Style: Heavy for the 
hungry. Setting: Plants, posters. Recommended dishes: Osso buco on pasta; roast 
pork loin stuffed with sausage. Cost per person: $10-$20. 
</P>
<P>
La Ve Lee, 12514 Ventura Blvd., Studio City. (818) 980-8158. Style: Continental 
dinner house with a Middle Eastern accent. Setting: Dim and cozy. Recommended 
dishes: Appetizer combo plate; shawarma. Cost per person: $15-$30. 
</P>
<P>
Ravel, Sheraton Grande Hotel, 333 S. Figueroa, Los Angeles. (213) 617-1133. 
Style: Continental mixed with cooking-school creative. Setting: Pluuussssh. 
Recommended dishes: Seared duck breast with mixed fruits; pepper steak with 
morels and crayfish. Cost per person: $30-$45. 
</P>
<P>
The Tower, Transamerica Tower, 1150 S. Olive St., Los Angeles. (213) 746-1554. 
Style: Rich, tender and uninvolving food with a view. Setting: Lots of windows. 
Recommended dishes: Capon Madagascar; steak tartare; salmon in filo. Cost per 
person: $30-$50. Kathie Jenkins 
</P>
