<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANOTHER NOMINATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I nominate "Rain Man's" producers and studio (United Artists) for best 
non-supporting performance of the year. 
</P>
<P>
The movie is about an autistic man. Great. And a big Beverly Hills benefit 
premiere was held. Wonderful; but wait: In an insensitive move, the premiere 
proceeds, more than $250,000, were given not to one of the severely underfunded 
efforts to unlock the mystery of autism but to a unrelated charity. 
</P>
<P>
Obviously, nobody involved with the benefit recognized the irony or, if they 
did, they didn't care enough to correct it. 
</P>
</TEXT>
