<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOV. DEUKMEJIAN ON STATE BUDGET AND TIMES RESPONSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I read Deukmejian's letter with great interest. I'm wondering why our governor, 
who's generally a nice, compassionate and understanding guy is so cruel and 
tight-fisted with our money, which really belongs to the people? 
</P>
<P>
Well, I believe that the answer lies in the recent political history. President 
Ronald Reagan cut taxes, decreased spending on social services, and all this 
has influenced many conservative politicians. Never mind that United States 
deficit has increased to horrible proportions, never mind the homeless, the 
mentally ill, the toxic dumps, the worn-out cities, the drugs, the street gangs 
and crime. Those politicians don't see that. They are hypnotized by the words 
of the Great Communicator, even though now we have different times, different 
problems. 
</P>
<P>
And that's the case with our governor. He's hypnotized. How will he get out of 
this state of hypnosis? I respectfully suggest that he take walks around Los 
Angeles slums, drive our freeways during rush hour, visit emergency services of 
county hospitals, visit our overcrowded schools and, perhaps, even visit our 
state hospitals and jails. He will learn something. At least, he will slip out 
of his state of blindness and rejection of facts. 
</P>
<P>
ADOLPH DONINS 
</P>
<P>
Oxnard 
</P>
