<HEADLINE>
<P>
ELDERLY SUICIDE: MORE THAN A MATTER OF LIFE AND DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Suicide Is a Tragic Secret for the Elderly." True, but think again. I would 
say Daniel Rosenthal chose the easiest way to go -- a quick death. I am 84 and 
I have no intention of just wasting away in a nursing home. When I cannot 
function as a normal human being, out I go. 
</P>
<P>
I have an idea that I hope will eventually be accepted by the civilized world: 
Let all of us who wish have hypodermic syringes filled with quick death, which 
we, ourselves, can inject in our veins. 
</P>
<P>
MADELEINE S. WILLIAMSON 
</P>
<P>
Malibu 
</P>
</TEXT>
