<P>
By SAM HALL KAPLAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Metropolis: The Architecture &amp; Design Magazine of New York" is looking 
beyond the Hudson, in response "to the desire for greater editorial and 
advertising coverage of California," says publisher Horace Havemeyer III, in 
the March issue. 
</P>
<P>
The magazine offered a tease for its expanded coverage in its January/February 
issue with an article on how MacArthur Place, a proposed Orange County 
development of Bell Canada Enterprises master-planned by New York-based urban 
designer M. Paul Friedberg, will cope with the car. It was the sort of article 
that serves a pre-leasing and pre-approval publicity effort well, albeit 
beginning with an obligatory freeway scene. 
</P>
