<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS BRIEFS: OFFICE LEASING RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By EVELYN DE WOLFE, From staff reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A record 3.9 million square feet of office space was leased in Orange County in 
the past year, according to a survey by Newport Economics Group. 
</P>
<P>
Most of the space, said the firm's president, Robert Dunham, was leased by 
large companies currently located in Orange County and expanding. 
</P>
<P>
Almost as much office space was built last year as was leased, Dunham said, so 
vacancy rates remained relatively high, registering 19.4% at the end of the 
year. 
</P>
<P>
As before, the John Wayne Airport area had the most construction and the most 
new tenants, but Irvine Spectrum has 1 million square feet under construction 
already committed to major tenants, he said. 
</P>
