<TEXT>
<P>
Also attending the Oscars will be Nancy Hale -- fresh from the kitchen. 
Producer Hale's "Portrait of Imogen" was nominated in the Best Documentary 
category, but it hasn't made her rich or famous. She spent recent weeks in her 
sister's Chicago gourmet shop and cafe, supervising a cooking crew and selling 
food delicacies to retail outlets. 
</P>
<P>
Hale, who has a baby daughter and a husband who is in grad school, moved from 
San Francisco to Chicago just before "Imogen's" release, convinced that "there 
was not enough money in making films to support a family. The films I did cost 
money rather than paying money." 
</P>
<P>
Now that her husband has finished his course work at Northwestern, the Hales 
plan to move back to California this fall. "Maybe I can make a living in film 
after all," she said, hopefully. From Stacy Jenel Smith 
