<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
SUSPECTED DRUG DEALER KILLED IN CANOGA PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A suspected drug peddler was shot to death Saturday following an apparent 
dispute with a customer behind a Canoga Park apartment house, Los Angeles 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
The 38-year-old victim, whose name was withheld until relatives can be 
notified, was identified as a transient from Nicaragua. 
</P>
<P>
Investigators said the man was shot several times in the 5:30 a.m. attack and 
was pronounced dead at the scene at the rear of apartments in the 21800 block 
of Lanark Street. 
</P>
<P>
The site is across from Lanark Park, which police have labeled "the worst area 
for open-air drug dealing" in the western San Fernando Valley. 
</P>
<P>
Neighbors said the victim slept in an apartment carport storage area and sold 
rock cocaine in an adjoining alley, Police Lt. Bill Gaida said. The dead man 
had been arrested in the past on suspicion of drug possession, Gaida said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
