<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WORLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Peruvian diplomat was charged with smuggling 44 pounds of cocaine, valued at 
$10.3 million, into Britain in a diplomatic pouch, a British official and 
Peruvian sources said. A Customs and Excise spokesman said Jose Manuel Pacheco 
Nunez, 30, who was not accredited to Britain, was arrested in a London hotel 
after arousing the suspicions of Customs officers at Heathrow airport. The 
spokesman said that because Pacheco is not accredited to Britain he does not 
enjoy diplomatic immunity. In Lima, Peruvian Foreign Minister Guillermo Larco 
Cox said Pacheco is a second-level diplomat who may be dismissed from the 
Foreign Service. Sources there said Pacheco was in charge of the ministry's 
computer system. 
</P>
</TEXT>
