<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WORLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Munich-based newspaper reported that a member of the West German Parliament 
from the ecological Greens party has links to a Libyan-financed foundation. 
Party leaders said they will investigate the allegations. Sueddeutsche Zeitung 
said Alfred Mechtersheimer is involved with the M.A.G. Foundation for Peace and 
Solidarity based in Vaduz, Liechstenstein. It said the foundation was financed 
by a $10-million account set up in Switzerland by Libyan leader Col. Moammar 
Kadafi. Mechtersheimer was quoted by the newspaper as saying he acted "as a 
kind of adviser" to the foundation, which was set up to promote the "new 
thinking" in Libya. 
</P>
