<TEXT>
<P>
Former Olympic diver Bruce Kimball's insurance companies have reached "an 
agreement in principle" to pay a total of $1.3 million to five victims of the 
car accident that killed two teen-agers and injured six others last August, 
Kimball's attorney, James A. Murman, said. 
</P>
<P>
Word of the agreement came a week before Kimball plans to ask a judge to reduce 
his 17-year prison sentence for drunk-driving manslaughter. Kimball, 25, is 
seeking a term of less than 10 years, which could mean a transfer out of 
maximum-security Tomoka Correctional Institution. 
</P>
