<HEADLINE>
<P>
NASCAR EVENT AT SAUGUS SPEEDWAY POSTPONED BY RAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Miller 125 at Saugus Speedway, the opening event of the 20-race NASCAR 
All-American Challenge Series Southwest Tour, was postponed Saturday because of 
inclement weather. The race will be rescheduled for an unspecified date. 
</P>
<P>
Other events postponed or canceled by rain Saturday included the opening round 
of the 16-team St. Paul Easter baseball tournament, which has been moved to 
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Crespi High will play at St. Bernard at 3 p.m. Monday and three games will be 
played at Blair Field in Long Beach: St. Genevieve vs. Alemany at 10 a.m., 
Chaminade vs. Loyola at 4 p.m. and Notre Dame vs. St. John Bosco at 7 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
But a nonconference college baseball game between Glendale and MiraCosta likely 
will not be rescheduled, Glendale Coach Steve Coots said. A NAIA District 3 
doubleheader between Cal Lutheran and Point Loma Nazarene has been rescheduled 
for Monday at noon at Cal Lutheran. 
</P>
<P>
A California Collegiate Athletic Assn. baseball game between Cal Poly San Luis 
Obispo and Cal State Northridge will be rescheduled for an unspecified date. 
</P>
<P>
And a CCAA softball doubleheader between Cal Poly SLO and CSUN has been 
rescheduled for April 23 at CSUN. 
</P>
</TEXT>
