<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: AZTECS TO PLAY TRIPLEHEADER AGAINST UTAH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rain forced the cancellation of the San Diego State-Utah Western Athletic 
Conference baseball doubleheader Saturday at SDSU, so the teams will play a 
tripleheader today at SDSU beginning at 10:30 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
SDSU defeated Utah, 3-2, Friday in the WAC opener for both. SDSU is 16-10, Utah 
5-14. 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
Joe McDonough defeated Ian Schroeder at No. 1 singles, 6-1, 6-4, and San Diego 
State went on to defeat the University of Washington, 6-1, in a UC Irvine 
tournament match. 
</P>
<P>
Tole Marinkovic and Jeff Belloli defeated Rob Grundy and Eric Freeman, 6-3, 
6-3, at No. 1 doubles for SDSU (7-12). Washington is 7-4. 
</P>
<P>
BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
The Chargers will play San Diego City College's Wheelchair Knights in a 
celebrity wheelchair basketball game Saturday at 1 p.m. in the San Diego High 
School gymnasium. 
</P>
<P>
Admission is $6 and tax deductible. Tickets may be purchased at the door or by 
calling 298-5824. Proceeds will be used to purchase a 1989 Chevrolet van, 
equipped with a wheelchair lift, that will be presented to the San Diego School 
District to transport physically handicapped children. 
</P>
<P>
RUNNING 
</P>
<P>
The Naval Amphibious Base Fleet Feet Running Club is sponsoring a 
five-kilometer run/walk April 9 to benefit the Navy Relief Society. The race 
will begin in Coronado and continue over the Bay Bridge into San Diego. 
Race-day registration is outside Gate 1 of the Naval Amphibious Base from 
5:30-6:45 a.m. Registration will also be held on April 8 at the Broadway Pier 
from 1-4 p.m. Call 437-2026 for information. 
</P>
