<HEADLINE>
<P>
NO LEADS DEVELOP IN ABDUCTION CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Placentia police said Saturday that they have no new leads on the abduction of 
a 65-year-old woman who was returned to anxious relatives Friday night, 7 hours 
after two men forced her into their van and sped away. 
</P>
<P>
The woman, Anelica Maria Perez, telephoned her family shortly before 9 p.m. 
from a fast-food restaurant in the City of Industry, where she told them her 
kidnapers had released her. 
</P>
<P>
Perez had been sweeping her front sidewalk at 3:12 p.m. Friday when the two men 
drove up and pulled her into the van, police and neighbors said. 
</P>
<P>
A neighbor gave chase in his vehicle and saw the van drive north on the Orange 
Freeway. He then alerted police. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
KIDNAPPINGS -- ORANGE COUNTY; POLICE INVESTIGATIONS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
