<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTY EVENTS ARE POSTPONED BECAUSE OF RAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rain caused the postponement of numerous Orange County athletic events 
scheduled for Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
UC Irvine tennis Coach Greg Patton called off play in the UC Irvine tennis 
tournament and rescheduled the matches for today. 
</P>
<P>
Patton spent most of the day shuffling back and forth between two phones in his 
office fielding calls from coaches regarding the final 19 matches. 
</P>
<P>
"This is a nightmare, I can't believe this (rain) is happening," said Patton. 
"It's going to be a marathon of tennis (Sunday). We're just going to be jamming 
all day." 
</P>
<P>
The contingency plan, provided rain does not interfere today, translates into a 
19-match schedule beginning at 7:15 a.m. The championship final is scheduled to 
begin at 1 p.m. at the UC Irvine tennis stadium. Other matches are scheduled to 
be played at the Newport Marriott, the Mesa Verde Tennis Club, the Balboa Bay 
Club, the Racquet Club of Irvine and Christ College Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
All games in the Pony softball tournament scheduled to be played Saturday at 
Cal State Fullerton were postponed until today. 
</P>
<P>
In the championship-round games, Cal State Fullerton, ranked No. 5 in the 
nation, will play Arizona, ranked No. 10, at 9:30 a.m. Akron plays Cal State 
Long Beach, ranked No. 11, also at 9:30. 
</P>
<P>
No. 3 Oklahoma State plays Cal Poly Pomona at 11 a.m., and No. 1 ranked Fresno 
State plays Texas A&amp;M, also at 11. 
</P>
<P>
Semifinal games are scheduled for 1 p.m. and the championship game is scheduled 
for 2:30 p.m. today. 
</P>
<P>
Also because of rain, the site of today's nonconference baseball game between 
UC Irvine and Minnesota has been changed from Irvine to Loyola Marymount, and 
the game will be played at 11 a.m. instead of noon. 
</P>
<P>
And the final games of the Saddleback College baseball tournament Saturday were 
canceled. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
RAIN; SCHEDULES; COLLEGE ATHLETICS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA032689-0205 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 36262 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
March 26, 1989, Sunday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
